---
import PortalLayout from '../layouts/PortalLayout.astro'
---

<PortalLayout
  title="Practitioner Network — Sohma Institute"
  description="A distributed clinical intelligence network of credentialed practitioners running shared protocols, contributing outcome data, and conferencing on complex cases across divisional boundaries."
>
  <article class="network-page">

    <!-- HERO -->
    <header class="network-hero">
      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Practitioner Network</div>
        <h1 class="hero-title">Distributed clinical intelligence.</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">The network isn't a professional association. It's not an alumni directory. It's an operational mesh — credentialed practitioners running shared protocols, feeding outcome data into a common registry, and conferencing on complex cases across divisional boundaries. Every member practises within a system that gets smarter because they participate.</p>

        <div class="hero-cta-row">
          <a href="/contact" class="hero-cta-primary">Apply to join network</a>
          <a href="#" class="hero-cta-secondary">Login to portal</a>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-join-grid">
          <a href="/contact" class="hero-join-card">
            <h3>I hold an Institute credential</h3>
            <p>Your credential determines your entry point — Affiliate, Associate, or Fellow.</p>
            <span class="hero-join-cta">Apply for membership &rarr;</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/education" class="hero-join-card">
            <h3>I don't hold a credential yet</h3>
            <p>The Foundation Certificate is a 12-week entry point into the network.</p>
            <span class="hero-join-cta">View education programs &rarr;</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/contact" class="hero-join-card">
            <h3>Enrolling a team or organisation</h3>
            <p>Institutional membership and group credentialing pathways available.</p>
            <span class="hero-join-cta">Contact for group enquiry &rarr;</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>


    <!-- THREE NETWORK TIERS -->
    <section class="tiers-section" id="tiers">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Network Tiers</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">You've earned the credential. Here's what you get access to.</p>

      <div class="tiers-grid">
        <div class="tier-card" data-accent="terracotta">
          <div class="tier-header">
            <div class="tier-badge">Affiliate</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Who</span>
            <p><a href="/education/foundation-certificate">Foundation Certificate</a> holders</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Access</span>
            <p>Tier A validated protocols. Continuing education program. Peer case conferencing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Role in the Network</span>
            <p>The broadest layer. Affiliates integrate Institute protocols into existing practice, contribute outcome data to the registry, and participate in peer case conferencing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Annual Membership</span>
            <p><a href="/contact">Enquire</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tier-card" data-accent="green">
          <div class="tier-header">
            <div class="tier-badge">Associate</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Who</span>
            <p><a href="/education/advanced-diploma">Advanced Diploma</a> holders</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Access</span>
            <p>Full protocol library including Tier B provisional protocols. Eligible to supervise Affiliates.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Role in the Network</span>
            <p>The clinical backbone. Associates practise within the Institute's framework at depth, supervise Affiliates, participate in quarterly case conferencing, and their clinical data carries more weight in the registry due to supervised training.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Annual Membership</span>
            <p><a href="/contact">Enquire</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tier-card" data-accent="warm">
          <div class="tier-header">
            <div class="tier-badge">Fellow</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Who</span>
            <p><a href="/education/fellowship">Fellowship</a> holders</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Access</span>
            <p>Protocol development privileges. Faculty appointment eligibility. Regional clinical governance leadership.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Role in the Network</span>
            <p>The governing layer. Fellows don't just use protocols — they develop them. They supervise Associates and Affiliates, lead regional governance, and are eligible for Institute faculty appointments.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-field">
            <span class="tier-field-label">Membership</span>
            <p>Included with Fellowship</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- NETWORK INFRASTRUCTURE -->
    <section class="infrastructure-section" id="infrastructure">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Network Infrastructure</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">What actually runs underneath the practitioner tiers.</p>

      <div class="infra-grid">
        <div class="infra-card">
          <div class="infra-icon">
            <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 12V7H5a2 2 0 0 1 0-4h14v4"/><path d="M3 5v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h16v-5"/><path d="M18 12a2 2 0 0 0 0 4h4v-4h-4z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Clinical Registry</h3>
          <div class="infra-detail">
            <div class="infra-field">
              <span class="infra-field-label">What it is</span>
              <p>Standardised outcome measurement deployed across every network practitioner. Every patient interaction using Institute protocols generates structured data.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="infra-field">
              <span class="infra-field-label">What it does</span>
              <p>De-identified data aggregation at scale. This is practice-based evidence generation — the registry is how the Institute builds its evidence base from real-world clinical outcomes rather than waiting for grant-funded trials.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="infra-field">
              <span class="infra-field-label">Why it matters to you</span>
              <p>You're not practising in isolation. Your clinical outcomes contribute to a growing dataset that refines the protocols you use. The evidence base improves because you participate.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="infra-field">
              <span class="infra-field-label">Where the data goes</span>
              <p>Feeds into the Cannabis Clinical Outcomes Registry and the broader protocol refinement pipeline. <a href="/research">See Research Programs &rarr;</a></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="infra-card">
          <div class="infra-icon">
            <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Case Conferencing System</h3>
          <div class="infra-detail">
            <div class="infra-field">
              <span class="infra-field-label">What it is</span>
              <p>Structured virtual case conferencing modelled on Medicare Team Care frameworks. Not informal peer discussion — a formalised system with presentation protocols, cross-divisional input, and documented outcomes.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="infra-field">
              <span class="infra-field-label">How it works</span>
              <p>Complex cases are presented cross-divisionally. A herbalist presents a case and gets input from a systems medicine practitioner and an environmental medicine specialist in the same session. This is where education, research, and clinical practice converge in real time.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="infra-field">
              <span class="infra-field-label">Frequency</span>
              <p>Peer conferencing for Affiliates. Quarterly structured conferencing for Associates. Fellows lead and facilitate.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="infra-field">
              <span class="infra-field-label">Why it matters</span>
              <p>Practitioners in private practice are typically isolated. This system makes the network's collective clinical intelligence available to every member, calibrated to their credential level.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- PROTOCOL ACCESS -->
    <section class="protocol-section" id="protocols">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Protocol Access</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">The Institute's clinical protocols are tiered by evidence maturity. Your network membership determines what you can access.</p>

      <div class="protocol-tiers">
        <div class="protocol-tier">
          <div class="protocol-badge validated">A</div>
          <div class="protocol-tier-body">
            <h3>Validated</h3>
            <p>Completed clinical pilot, peer-reviewed, distributed network-wide. Available to all network members.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="protocol-tier-detail">
            <p>Validated protocols have completed at least one supervised clinical pilot with documented outcomes, undergone internal peer review, and demonstrated reproducible results across multiple practitioners. These are the protocols the network stands behind — they represent the Institute's best current understanding of effective clinical practice in their domain.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="protocol-tier">
          <div class="protocol-badge provisional">B</div>
          <div class="protocol-tier-body">
            <h3>Provisional</h3>
            <p>Active clinical pilot, preliminary data. Available to Associates and Fellows under supervision framework.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="protocol-tier-detail">
            <p>Provisional protocols are in active clinical testing. Preliminary outcome data looks promising, but the evidence base isn't yet sufficient for network-wide distribution. Associates and Fellows can implement these under the supervision framework, and their clinical data feeds directly into the validation pipeline. This is where practitioners contribute most directly to the Institute's evidence base.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="protocol-tier">
          <div class="protocol-badge investigational">C</div>
          <div class="protocol-tier-body">
            <h3>Investigational</h3>
            <p>Research design phase. Available only within research settings. Not distributed through the network.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="protocol-tier-detail">
            <p>Investigational protocols are still in the research design phase — being developed from literature synthesis, preclinical evidence, or clinical observation. They haven't entered formal clinical piloting yet. Access is restricted to research settings, and they are not distributed through the practitioner network until they advance to Tier B.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="protocol-crosslink">These tiers connect to the <a href="/research">clinical translation pipeline</a> — protocols move from C to B to A as evidence accumulates.</p>
    </section>





  </article>
</PortalLayout>

<style>
  .network-page {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    padding: 0;
  }
  .network-page p { line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .network-page p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .network-page h2, .network-page h3 { margin: 0; }
  .network-page a { color: var(--accent-dark); text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.15s; }
  .network-page a:hover { color: var(--accent-darker-hover); }

  :global(.reading-progress) { display: none !important; }
  .network-page a.hero-cta-primary,
  .network-page a.hero-cta-primary:hover { color: var(--text-on-dark); }

  /* ═══════════ HERO ═══════════ */
  .network-hero {
    position: relative;
    max-width: none;
    margin: 0 -40px;
    padding: 0;
    background: var(--bg-hero);
    overflow: visible;
  }

  .hero-inner {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 96px calc(2rem + 40px) 64px calc(1rem + 40px);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .section-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .section-label::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--accent-line);
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4.25rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }

  .hero-lead {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 640px;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Hero CTAs */
  .hero-cta-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero-cta-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--text-on-dark);
    background: var(--accent-dark);
    padding: 12px 28px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }

  .hero-cta-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-darker-hover);
    color: var(--text-on-dark);
  }

  .hero-cta-secondary {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-medium);
    padding: 12px 28px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, color 0.15s;
  }

  .hero-cta-secondary:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent-dark);
    color: var(--accent-dark);
  }

  /* Hero join cards */
  .hero-join-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .hero-join-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }

  .hero-join-card:hover {
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
  }

  .hero-join-card + .hero-join-card {
    border-left: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .hero-join-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .hero-join-card p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .hero-join-cta {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
  }

  .hero-join-card:hover .hero-join-cta {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }


  /* ═══════════ SECTION HEADINGS ═══════════ */
  .network-page .section-heading {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .network-page .section-intro {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }


  /* ═══════════ NETWORK TIERS ═══════════ */
  .tiers-section {
    padding: 4rem 0 4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .tiers-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    grid-template-rows: auto;
    gap: 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .tier-card {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-rows: subgrid;
    grid-row: span 5; /* header + 4 fields */
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .tier-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
  }

  /* Accent left border + hover */
  [data-accent="terracotta"] { border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-dark); }
  [data-accent="green"] { border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-green); }
  [data-accent="warm"] { border-left: 3px solid var(--chart-warm); }

  [data-accent="terracotta"]:hover { border-color: var(--accent-dark); }
  [data-accent="green"]:hover { border-color: var(--accent-green); }
  [data-accent="warm"]:hover { border-color: var(--chart-warm); }

  .tier-header {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  [data-accent="terracotta"] .tier-header { background: var(--accent-bg-04); }
  [data-accent="green"] .tier-header { background: rgba(104,124,87,0.05); }
  [data-accent="warm"] .tier-header { background: var(--chart-warm-bg-subtle); }

  .tier-badge {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  [data-accent="terracotta"] .tier-badge { color: var(--accent-dark); }
  [data-accent="green"] .tier-badge { color: var(--accent-green); }
  [data-accent="warm"] .tier-badge { color: var(--chart-warm); }

  .tier-field {
    padding: 1rem 1.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .tier-field:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  /* Last field (membership) gets a subtle tinted footer bg */
  [data-accent="terracotta"] .tier-field:last-child { background: var(--accent-bg-02); }
  [data-accent="green"] .tier-field:last-child { background: rgba(104,124,87,0.02); }
  [data-accent="warm"] .tier-field:last-child { background: rgba(158,122,74,0.03); }

  .tier-field-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  /* Field labels inherit tier accent color */
  [data-accent="terracotta"] .tier-field-label { color: var(--accent-dark); opacity: 0.7; }
  [data-accent="green"] .tier-field-label { color: var(--accent-green); opacity: 0.7; }
  [data-accent="warm"] .tier-field-label { color: var(--chart-warm); opacity: 0.8; }

  .tier-field p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-body-65);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }


  /* ═══════════ INFRASTRUCTURE ═══════════ */
  .infrastructure-section {
    padding: 4rem 0 4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .infra-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .infra-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 0;
    padding: 2rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .infra-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent-border-15);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
  }

  .infra-icon {
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .infra-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .infra-field {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .infra-field:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .infra-field-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    opacity: 0.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .infra-field p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-body-60);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }


  /* ═══════════ PROTOCOL ACCESS ═══════════ */
  .protocol-section {
    padding: 4rem 0 4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .protocol-tiers {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .protocol-tier {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr 1.5fr;
    align-items: start;
    gap: 0 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 0;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .protocol-tier:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent-border-15);
  }

  .protocol-tier-detail {
    border-left: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .protocol-tier-detail p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .protocol-badge {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  .protocol-badge.validated {
    color: #fff;
    background: var(--accent-green);
  }

  .protocol-badge.provisional {
    color: #fff;
    background: var(--chart-blue);
  }

  .protocol-badge.investigational {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-medium);
  }

  .protocol-tier-body h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .protocol-tier-body p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-body-60);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .protocol-crosslink {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-body-50);
  }






  /* ═══════════ RESPONSIVE ═══════════ */
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .network-hero {
      margin: 0 -20px;
    }

    .hero-inner {
      padding: 64px calc(1.5rem + 20px) 48px calc(1rem + 20px);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner {
      padding: 48px 1.25rem 36px;
    }

    .hero-title {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .hero-lead {
      padding-left: 0;
    }

    .tiers-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      grid-template-rows: auto;
    }

    .tier-card {
      grid-row: auto;
      grid-template-rows: none;
    }

    .infra-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .hero-join-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0;
    }

    .hero-join-card + .hero-join-card {
      border-left: none;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    }

    .protocol-tier {
